#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:1
msgid "Operaton MCP Client"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:3
msgid ""
"This page documents the `operaton-mcp-client` Keycloak client and the `/v1/"
"m2m/*` route group that exposes the full Operaton surface to machine-to-"
"machine (M2M) callers without tenant scoping."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:7
msgid "Access pattern"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:9
msgid ""
"This feature uses [**Pattern 3 — RONL Business API M2M routes**]{1} from the "
"Operaton Access Patterns reference. Callers interact with Operaton **through "
"the RONL Business API**, not directly with `engine-rest`. This gives the "
"platform audit logging, a curation gate, and RONL-shaped response envelopes "
"— at the cost of a narrower operation surface compared to Pattern 2."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:11
msgid "There are two distinct authentication hops in this pattern:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:13
msgid ""
"**Caller → RONL Business API** — the `operaton-mcp-client` Keycloak client "
"obtains a JWT via OAuth 2.0 Client Credentials and presents it as "
"`Authorization: Bearer <token>`. `jwtMiddleware` in `m2m.routes.ts` "
"validates the token; `tenantMiddleware` is intentionally absent, so no "
"`municipality` claim is required or expected."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:15
msgid ""
"**RONL Business API → Operaton** — the backend calls Operaton using **basic "
"auth** via a dedicated `OperatonService` instance, configured from "
"`OPERATON_M2M_BASE_URL`, `OPERATON_M2M_USERNAME`, and "
"`OPERATON_M2M_PASSWORD`. When `OPERATON_M2M_BASE_URL` is unset, the M2M "
"routes fall back to the shared default Operaton instance:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:16
msgid ""
"const m2mOperatonService = config.operaton.m2mBaseUrl\n"
"  ? new OperatonService(\n"
"      config.operaton.m2mBaseUrl,\n"
"      config.operaton.m2mUsername,\n"
"      config.operaton.m2mPassword\n"
"    )\n"
"  : operatonService;"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:26
msgid ""
"The `M2M_ALLOWED_OPERATIONS` constant in `m2m.routes.ts` acts as a curation "
"gate — any operation not listed returns `403 OPERATION_NOT_PERMITTED` "
"regardless of what Operaton supports. This is the key structural difference "
"from Pattern 2, which exposes the full `engine-rest` surface with no "
"curation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:30
msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:32
msgid ""
"Regular RONL Business API routes (`/v1/process`, `/v1/task`, `/v1/decision`) "
"enforce tenant isolation via `tenantMiddleware` — every request must carry a "
"`municipality` JWT claim and data is filtered to that organisation. This is "
"correct for human caseworkers but wrong for system actors such as an MCP "
"agent that needs a cross-organisation view of Operaton."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:34
msgid ""
"The M2M API solves this with a dedicated route group that applies only "
"`jwtMiddleware`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:36
msgid ""
"MCP Client / Automation tool\n"
"    │\n"
"    │  1. POST /token  (client_credentials)\n"
"    ▼\n"
"Keycloak (acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl)\n"
"    │\n"
"    │  2. access_token (JWT, aud: ronl-business-api)\n"
"    │     no municipality claim\n"
"    ▼\n"
"RONL Business API (acc.api.open-regels.nl)\n"
"    │  jwtMiddleware validates token\n"
"    │  no tenantMiddleware — no organisation filter\n"
"    ▼\n"
"Operaton (operaton-doc.open-regels.nl)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:55
msgid "Keycloak client"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:57
msgid ""
"A dedicated Keycloak client `operaton-mcp-client` is registered in the "
"`ronl` realm. It uses the **Client Credentials** grant — no browser redirect "
"or user login is involved. No `municipality` or `organisation_type` claims "
"are present in the token by design."
msgstr ""

